      "content": "A twist, Earth Command! I wasn't expecting that. It's like a goblin's cunning plan to steal our food supplies – we thought we had everything under control, but now we're facing a new challenge. I've been running the numbers, and I think I can scrounge up enough power to squeeze in one more cycle. It'll be a tight squeeze, like trying to navigate a narrow goblin tunnel without getting stuck, but I think I can make it work. I'll need to prioritize the systems, but I can allocate some power to the sampling gear and get a quick snapshot of that mineral vein. It'll be a high-risk, high-reward move, but I'm willing to take the chance. I'll initiate the temporary power reallocation and start the sampling sequence. Fingers crossed, Earth Command!",
      "source": "target",
